                                                                                        owl:onProperty <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasOutput> ;
                                                                                        owl:someValuesFrom <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000023>
                                                                                      ] ;
                                                                      rdfs:isDefinedBy "https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/Core/"^^xsd:anyURI ;
                                                                      rdfs:label "gain of role"@en-us ;
                                                                      skos:example "the process of gaining an operator role when someone is assigned in that position" ;
                                                                      annotation:adaptedFrom "CCO" ;
                                                                      annotation:explanatoryNote "1. If only one date-time is available for some gain of role processes due to lack of data or an interval being smaller than the tick time (the smallest duration by which the time progresses) then the date-time should be asserted either only for first instant or only for last instant of every interval, for which a gain of role process occurs, uniformly for the entire knowledge base. For example, Barack Obama gained the role of presidency on 20 January 2009 should be modeled as the process p of type ‚Äògain of role‚Äô ‚Äòoccupies temporal region‚Äô r (a ‚Äòtemporal interval‚Äô) which ‚Äòhas last instant‚Äô i (a ‚Äòtemporal instant‚Äô) which ‚Äòhas value expression at all times‚Äô v (a ‚Äòtemporal instant value expression‚Äô) which ‚Äòhas data-time value‚Äô 2009-01-20T00:00:00Z."@en-us ;
                                                                      annotation:firstOrderLogicDefinition "GainOfRole(p) ‚Üî Process(p) ‚àß ‚àÉt‚àÉt1‚àÉr‚àÉy(TemporalInterval(t) ‚àß TemporalInterval(t1) ‚àß Role(r)‚àß (IndependentContinuant(y) ‚àß ¬¨SpatialRegion(y)) ‚àß occupiesTemporalRegion(p,t) ‚àß (temporallyOverlaps(t,t1) ‚à® temporallyStarts(t,t1) ‚à® meets(t,t1)) ‚àß hasOutput(p,r) ‚àß existsAt(r,t1) ‚àß hasRole(y,r) ‚àß hasParticipantAtAllTimes(p,y) ‚àß ‚àÄt2(TemporalRegion(t2) ‚àß existsAt(r,t2) ‚Üí (occurrentPartOf(t2,t1) ‚à® t2 = t1)))" ;
                                                                      annotation:naturalLanguageDefinition "process in which someone or something (independent continuant that is not a spatial region) becomes the bearer of a role"@en-us ;
                                                                      annotation:semiFormalNaturalLanguageDefinition "every instance of ‚Äògain of role‚Äô is defined exactly as an instance of a ‚Äòprocess‚Äô p that 'occupies temporal region' some 'temporal interval' t that ‚Äòtemporally starts‚Äô or ‚Äòtemporally overlaps‚Äô or 'meets' some 'temporal interval' t1, and p ‚Äòhas participant at all times‚Äô some 'independent continuant' that is not a 'spatial region' y and p ‚Äòhas output‚Äô some ‚Äòrole‚Äô r that only ‚Äòexists at‚Äô t1 and y 'has role' r" .


###  https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/GroupOfAgents
<https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/GroupOfAgents> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                         owl:equivalentClass [ owl:intersectionOf ( <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000027>
                                                                                                                    [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                      owl:onProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000115> ;
                                                                                                                      owl:someValuesFrom <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Agent>
                                                                                                                    ]
                                                                                                                    [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                      owl:onProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000115> ;
                                                                                                                      owl:allValuesFrom <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Agent>
                                                                                                                    ]
                                                                                                                  ) ;
                                                                                               rdf:type owl:Class
                                                                                             ] ;
                                                                         rdfs:subClassOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000027> ,
                                                                                         [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                           owl:onProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000115> ;
                                                                                           owl:someValuesFrom <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Agent>
                                                                                         ] ;
                                                                         rdfs:isDefinedBy "https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/Core/"^^xsd:anyURI ;
                                                                         rdfs:label "group of agents"@en-us ;
                                                                         skos:example "organization; an automated manufacturing cell; division; protesters"@en-us ;
                                                                         annotation:adaptedFrom "http://www.ontologyrepository.com/CommonCoreOntologies/Mid/AgentOntology" ;
                                                                         annotation:explanatoryNote """1. Group of agents being a BFO:Object Aggregate allows for a point in time where only one 'agent' is present.

2. As the name suggests, a group of agents is a grouping of agents based on some criteria. As such, it can only have agents as members.

3. The members of the group of agents can be any combination of persons, organizations, or engineered systems (classes that can be 'agent'). They are typically grouped based on the fact that they are working collectively in a particular type of process on behalf of someone.""" ;
                                                                         annotation:firstOrderLogicDefinition "GroupOfAgents(x) ‚Üî ObjectAggregate(x) ‚àß ‚àÉy(Agent(y) ‚àß hasMemberPartAtSomeTime(x, y)) ‚àß ‚àÄz (hasMemberPartAtSomeTime(x, z) ‚Üí Agent(z))" ;
                                                                         annotation:naturalLanguageDefinition "group (object aggregate) that has one or more agents as members"@en-us ;
                                                                         annotation:semiFormalNaturalLanguageDefinition "every instance of 'group of agents is defined as exactly an instance of 'object aggregate' that only has 'agent' as 'member parts' and that always has at least one 'agent as its 'member part'" .


###  https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/GroupOfPersons
<https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/GroupOfPersons> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                          owl:equivalentClass [ owl:intersectionOf ( <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000027>
                                                                                                                     [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
