                                                                      rdfs:isDefinedBy "https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/Core/"^^xsd:anyURI ;
                                                                      rdfs:label "loss of role"@en-us ;
                                                                      skos:example "the process of losing a student role when a student graduates" ;
                                                                      annotation:adaptedFrom "CCO" ;
                                                                      annotation:explanatoryNote "1. If only one date-time is available for some loss of role processes due to lack of data or an interval being smaller than the tick time (the smallest duration by which the time progresses) then the date-time should be asserted either only for first instant or only for last instant of every interval, for which a loss of role process occurs, uniformly for the entire knowledge base. For example, Bill Clinton lost the role of presidency on 19 December 1998 should be modeled as the process p of type ‚Äòloss of role‚Äô ‚Äòoccupies temporal region‚Äô r (a ‚Äòtemporal interval‚Äô) which ‚Äòhas first instant‚Äô i (a ‚Äòtemporal instant‚Äô) which ‚Äòhas value expression at all times‚Äô v (a ‚Äòtemporal instant value expression‚Äô) which ‚Äòhas data-time value‚Äô 1998-12-19T00:00:00Z."@en-us ;
                                                                      annotation:firstOrderLogicDefinition "LossOfRole(p) ‚Üî Process(p) ‚àß ‚àÉt‚àÉt1‚àÉr‚àÉy(TemporalInterval(t) ‚àß TemporalInterval(t1) ‚àß Role(r) ‚àß (IndependentContinuant(y) ‚àß ¬¨SpatialRegion(y)) ‚àß occupiesTemporalRegion(p,t) ‚àß (isTemporallyOverlappedBy(t,t1) ‚à® temporallyFinishes(t,t1) ‚à® metBy(t,t1)) ‚àß hasInput(p,r) ‚àß existsAt(r,t1) ‚àß hasRole(y,r) ‚àß hasParticipantAtAllTimes(p,y) ‚àß ‚àÄt2(TemporalRegion(t2) ‚àß existsAt(r,t2) ‚Üí (occurrentPartOf(t2,t1) ‚à® t2 = t1)))" ;
                                                                      annotation:naturalLanguageDefinition "process in which someone or something (independent continuant that is not a spatial region) ceases to be the bearer of a role"@en-us ;
                                                                      annotation:semiFormalNaturalLanguageDefinition "every instance of ‚Äòloss of role‚Äô is defined exactly as an instance of a ‚Äòprocess‚Äô p that 'occupies temporal region' some 'temporal interval' t that ‚Äòtemporally finishes‚Äô or 'is temporally overlapped by‚Äô or is 'met by' some 'temporal interval' t1 and p ‚Äòhas participant at all times‚Äô some 'independent continuant' that is not a 'spatial region' y, and p ‚Äòhas input‚Äô some ‚Äòrole‚Äô r that only ‚Äòexists at‚Äô t1 and y 'has role' r" .


###  https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaintainableMaterialItem
<https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaintainableMaterialItem> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                    owl:equivalentClass [ owl:intersectionOf ( [ rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                                                                 owl:unionOf ( <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/EngineeredSystem>
                                                                                                                                               <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact>
                                                                                                                                             )
                                                                                                                               ]
                                                                                                                               [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                                                 owl:onProperty <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasRole> ;
                                                                                                                                 owl:someValuesFrom <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaintainableMaterialItemRole>
                                                                                                                               ]
                                                                                                                             ) ;
                                                                                                          rdf:type owl:Class
                                                                                                        ] ;
                                                                                    rdfs:subClassOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000040> ,
                                                                                                    [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                      owl:onProperty <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasRole> ;
                                                                                                      owl:someValuesFrom <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaintainableMaterialItemRole>
                                                                                                    ] ;
                                                                                    rdfs:isDefinedBy "https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/Core/"^^xsd:anyURI ;
                                                                                    rdfs:label "maintainable material item"@en-us ;
                                                                                    skos:example "CNC machine on which routine maintenance is performed"@en-us ;
                                                                                    annotation:explanatoryNote "See the expanded definition under the corresponding role class. The term is formalized here as a defined class by referring to its corresponding role class and exists primarily for ontological modeling and implementation convenience." ;
                                                                                    annotation:firstOrderLogicDefinition "MaintainableMaterialItem(x) ‚Üî (MaterialArtifact(x) ‚à® EngineeredSystem(x)) ‚àß ‚àÉr (MaintainableMaterialItemRole(r) ‚àß hasRole(x,r))" ;
                                                                                    annotation:naturalLanguageDefinition "material artifact or engineered system which has the maintainable material item role"@en-us ;
                                                                                    annotation:semiFormalNaturalLanguageDefinition "every instance of 'maintainable material item' is defined as exactly an instance of 'material artifact' or an 'engineered system' which 'has role' some 'maintainable material item role'" .


###  https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaintainableMaterialItemRole
<https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaintainableMaterialItemRole> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                        rdfs:subClassOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000023> ;
                                                                                        rdfs:isDefinedBy "https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/Core/"^^xsd:anyURI ;
                                                                                        rdfs:label "maintainable material item role"@en-us ;
                                                                                        skos:example "a CNC machine has the maintainable material item role when it is undergoing repair after a failure"@en-us ;
                                                                                        annotation:adaptedFrom "https://ceur-ws.org/Vol-2900/WS5Paper2.pdf" ;
                                                                                        annotation:firstOrderLogicAxiom "MaintainableMaterialItemRole(x) ‚Üí Role(x)" ;
                                                                                        annotation:isPrimitive "true"^^xsd:boolean ;
                                                                                        annotation:naturalLanguageDefinition "role played by an asset (engineered system or material artifact) when there is a maintenance strategy prescribing its maintenance process"@en-us ;
                                                                                        annotation:primitiveRationale "There are insufficient constructs to create necessary and sufficient conditions. Namely, constructs for 'maintenance strategy' and 'maintenance process' need to be formalized." ;
                                                                                        annotation:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom "if x is a 'maintainable material item' then x is a 'role'" .


###  https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Manufacturer
<https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Manufacturer> rdf:type owl:Class ;
